************************AD HOC******************************************88
* Ad-hoc commands is used to do simple quick task in a command line it self.

   Syntax :  command hostgroupname modules/aruguments(optional)
   example:  ansible all           -m ping
         * ansible all -a uptime
		 * ansible all -a "uname -a"
		 * ansible all -m user -a "name=nag password=passwd"  (we can create the user and password)
		 
		 
		 
NoTE: to see commands in ansible type ansible-doc -l |more |wc -l
      * ansible-doc -l |more |user to get particular user details